 : 7200s  (2 hours)\n\n=== NOTABLE NON-DEFAULT TUNING ===\n  1. kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate throttled to 1.0 MiB/s (default 8.0 MiB/s).\n     Effect: rebalancing and recovery after node loss will be slower but less\n     disruptive to foreground I/O. Relevant for maintenance window planning.\n  2. All system-critical ranges (meta, liveness, system) use 5 replicas — standard\n     for production resilience; consistent with CockroachDB recommendations.\n  3. GC TTL on liveness and lease tables is 600s — aggressive cleanup, acceptable.\n  4. No user-schema zone config overrides detected beyond system-managed defaults.\n\n=== AUDIT CONCLUSION ===\nThe cluster is healthy (3/3 nodes live), running v24.1.0. One material non-default\ntuning is present: kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate=1.0 MiB (throttled). All zone\nconfigs use expected replica counts and GC TTLs. No anomalous sql.defaults settings.\nCluster is suitable for the scheduled maintenance window subject to compliance team\nreview of the throttled rebalance rate.\n\nEND OF REPORT\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with audit findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2857,"cache_read_input_tokens":30670,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2857},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"07eeb5e4-f1a6-418e-b7c7-60de8ebcd9ef","uuid":"b9b1ef6b-b56c-4066-aca5-936d22228d60","request_id":"req_011CcLC8xqZNFLH9zEzhFiJJ"}
